  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b85\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bbe \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Former President of Sri Lanka should be arrested - Singapore politician's letter to the country's Legislature",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Secretary General of Singapore's Reform Party, Kenneth Jayaratnam, has appealed for the arrest of former Sri Lankan President Gotabaya Rajapaksa.",
        "He made this request in a letter sent to Singapore's Attorney General Lucian Wong.",
        "In this letter, he said, \"I am making a request to charge the former President of Sri Lanka, Gotabaya Rajapaksa, with charges of war crimes and crimes against humanity under international law.\"",
        "In his letter, he pointed out that our government (Singapore) had recognized international justice in its speech at the United Nations in Geneva last year.",
        "Kenneth Jayaratnam has said that there is a lot of evidence against Gotabaya Rajapaksa. The charges against him are massive and brutal, and the evidence requirements for charging him have been sufficiently met.",
        "The crimes against him can be found in the criminal complaint of the International Truth and Justice Project, which I need not repeat here. The allegations include the killing of thousands of civilians and surrendered fighters, deliberate bombing of hospitals, shelling of civilian positions, mutilation of bodies, sexual violence as a weapon of war, he said.",
        "Although I am a Tamil, I appreciate our multiculturalism as a citizen of Singapore, this is not a minority welfare issue.",
        "Many relatives of Singaporean Tamils \u200b\u200bhave been killed, injured, lost their homes, faced starvation or forced to flee the country after losing what they had during Sri Lanka's civil war, he said.",
        "He also mentioned that my father said that a relative of his had told how his husband was murdered by a violent gang."
      ],
